text: Josef Gottfried Ignaz Kainz (2 January 1858 - 20 September 1910) was an Austrian actor. He was one of the greatest actors of the German-speaking theatre. He was known for his works in Hamlet, Richard II, Schiller's Don Carlos and as Franz Moor in The Robbers. ==References== Category:1858 births Category:1910 deaths Category:Deaths from cancer Category:Austrian stage actors Category:Actors from Vienna
